    a:'• Bromine has a <strong>smaller relative molecular mass</strong><br>• So bromine has <strong>weaker intermolecular forces</strong><br>• So bromine has a <strong>melting point below room temperature</strong> (and pressure)', marks:'3 marks' },

  { id:11, topic:'q4',  tag:'tag-q4',  label:'Q4a · Electrolysis',
    q:'Which row is correct for the electrolysis of an ionic compound?\nA: no/no  B: no/yes  C: yes/no  D: yes/yes\n(molten / solid)',
